with everything--

00:26:12,513 --> 00:26:14,682
and that's 18 slices-- and
a full liter of cherry soda.

00:26:15,883 --> 00:26:17,051
If it matters, they sat

00:26:17,117 --> 00:26:18,385
in the parking lot
for a while.

00:26:18,452 --> 00:26:20,154
Is there anything you can
remember about the car?

00:26:20,221 --> 00:26:21,322
Make? Color?

00:26:21,388 --> 00:26:22,556
It was a Mercury Marquis.

00:26:22,623 --> 00:26:24,725
Are you positive?
Yeah.

00:26:24,792 --> 00:26:26,160
My boyfriend's a street...

00:26:26,227 --> 00:26:28,529
uh, he's into cars, so...

00:26:28,596 --> 00:26:30,297
I know cars.

00:26:31,732 --> 00:26:33,734
No sand in his nasal
passages or lungs.

00:26:33,801 --> 00:26:35,636
He was dead before
he was buried.

00:26:37,304 --> 00:26:39,974
Are those palm prints
on his sternum?

00:26:40,040 --> 00:26:43,010
Consistent in position
and pressure with CPR.

00:26:43,077 --> 00:26:44,545
Also found air in his stomach.

00:26:44,612 --> 00:26:46,347
<i>If you don't tilt</i>
<i>the head back,</i>

00:26:46,413 --> 00:26:47,748
<i>the trachea doesn't open.</i>

00:26:47,815 --> 00:26:49,950
<i>It forces air into the stomach</i>
<i>instead of the lungs</i>

00:26:50,017 --> 00:26:51,752
<i>and that's bad CPR.</i>

00:26:51,819 --> 00:26:54,088
Now, what kind of a killer

00:26:54,155 --> 00:26:55,489
performs CPR
on their victim?

00:26:55,556 --> 00:26:57,858
Well, maybe he didn't
mean to kill him.

00:26:57,925 --> 00:27:00,561
His pupils were dilated.

00:27:00,628 --> 00:27:01,695
I found a
subdural hematoma

00:27:01,762 --> 00:27:03,531
in the left
frontal lobe.

00:27:03,597 --> 00:27:05,232
That's your preliminary
cause of death.

00:27:05,299 --> 00:27:07,468
I sent samples to
Tox, of course.

00:27:07,535 --> 00:27:09,537
Catherine found
blood smear

00:27:09,603 --> 00:27:11,539
on the floor
where he was playing.

00:27:11,605 --> 00:27:14,408
He has a laceration
on his cheek.

00:27:14,475 --> 00:27:16,544
And the grandpa admits
he pushed Lucas down

00:27:16,610 --> 00:27:18,712
when he hit his head.
Except that, by itself,

00:27:18,779 --> 00:27:20,648
the head injury wouldn't
have been immediately fatal

00:27:20,714 --> 00:27:23,417
or necessarily
incapacitating.

00:27:23,484 --> 00:27:26,453
But, yeah, he would've
had a headache.

00:27:29,290 --> 00:27:32,059
Hey, got some gasoline
samples for you.

00:27:32,126 --> 00:27:34,528
Thanks, Greg. It's gonna
take a little while
to fill my tank.

00:27:34,595 --> 00:27:35,563
Why don't I get
you a funnel?

00:27:35,629 --> 00:27:37,064
Kidding.

00:27:37,131 --> 00:27:38,465
You think your arson case

00:27:38,532 --> 00:27:39,600
has something to do
with these missing kids?

00:27:39,667 --> 00:27:41,969
Well, Carl Fisher lives
in the neighborhood,

00:27:42,036 --> 00:27:43,871
but, so far,
his alibi checks out.

00:27:43,938 --> 00:27:47,274
I don't know why pedophiles
just don't kill themselves.

00:27:47,341 --> 00:27:49,076
Who knows,
he might have tried.

00:27:49,143 --> 00:27:50,344
I collected these

00:27:50,411 --> 00:27:52,146
from service stations
closest to his house.

00:27:52,213 --> 00:27:53,280
Did you consider...

00:27:53,347 --> 00:27:55,416
That he might have filled up
on his way to work

00:27:55,483 --> 00:27:56,851
or anywhere else in Vegas?

00:27:56,917 --> 00:27:58,052
Yes-- that's why

00:27:58,118 --> 00:28:00,154
I wanted to get you
started on these

00:28:00,221 --> 00:28:02,189
before I hit the other
stations on the list.

00:28:02,256 --> 00:28:04,258
Good job, gas-hopper.

00:28:09,263 --> 00:28:11,265
Okay, then...

00:28:12,733 --> 00:28:16,003
...what would you do

00:28:16,070 --> 00:28:18,172
if you were going
to take those boys?

00:28:18,239 --> 00:28:20,708
I would be studying them.

00:28:20,774 --> 00:28:23,310
Do they like sports?
Comic books?

00:28:23,377 --> 00:28:26,480
Do they skip school?
Have any friends?

00:28:26,547 --> 00:28:28,582
Good parents,
or are they neglected?

00:28:28,649 --> 00:28:29,984
Unhappy? Angry?

00:28:30,050 --> 00:28:31,685
And then?

00:28:31,752 --> 00:28:33,954
What do you do
when you like a woman?

00:28:34,021 --> 00:28:36,123
It's a game of seduction.

00:28:36,190 --> 00:28:39,727
Once you know what they like,
you make contact.

00:28:39,793 --> 00:28:41,795
You start slowly, play it cool.

00:28:41,862 --> 00:28:43,030
Especially with boys.

00:28:43,097 --> 00:28:46,033
It's about building trust.

00:28:47,635 --> 00:28:49,403
Like you're doing with me.

00:28:50,437 --> 00:28:52,506
Do you like mushrooms, Carl?

00:28:52,573 --> 00:28:54,742
I like all
the nightshade vegetables.

00:28:54,809 --> 00:28:56,043
Are you going to buy me dinner?

00:28:59,079 --> 00:29:01,615
We found mushrooms
in the backseat of your car.

00:29:01,682 --> 00:29:03,818
Is this turning
into an interrogation?

00:29:06,253 --> 00:29:08,055
You're free to leave.

00:29:11,025 --> 00:29:12,293
On the night the
boys disappeared,

00:29:12,359 --> 00:29:14,695
witnesses said they saw
them sitting in a car

00:29:14,762 --> 00:29:17,698
with a man,
eating pizza.

00:29:17,765 --> 00:29:21,035
You take a date out
to a nice steak dinner.

00:29:21,101 --> 00:29:22,703
Kids would rather have

00:29:22,770 --> 00:29:24,705
hamburgers or pizza.

00:29:24,772 --> 00:29:27,208
Did you take the kids
out for pizza?

00:29:27,274 --> 00:29:30,811
No, I'm talking hypothetically.

00:29:30,878 --> 00:29:32,313
You must be desperate

00:29:32,379 --> 00:29:33,981
for a suspect,
or a scapegoat.

00:29:34,048 --> 00:29:37,151
Do you need to give the press
something to chew on?

00:29:37,218 --> 00:29:39,720
We just found
Lucas Hanson's dead body.

00:29:39,787 --> 00:29:41,455
They're chewing on that.

00:29:44,792 --> 00:29:46,427
What about the other boy?

00:29:46,494 --> 00:29:48,929
He's still missing.

00:29:48,996 --> 00:29:52,299
In my opinion,
if someone killed one boy...

00:29:53,801 --> 00:29:55,603
...he'd kill them both.

00:30:05,913 --> 00:30:08,982
So, we're working on a couple
of Jason sightings.

00:30:09,049 --> 00:30:11,618
Camper in Red Rock
spotted a kid

00:30:11,685 --> 00:30:13,687
that looks like Jason,
so I sent Vega.

00:30:13,754 --> 00:30:16,490
And Sofia is on her way
to Bullhead City, Arizona.

00:30:16,556 --> 00:30:18,792
A woman on a bus
called the cops.

00:30:18,859 --> 00:30:20,794
She swears that Jason's
sitting next to her.

00:30:20,861 --> 00:30:22,663
That's what I've got.

00:30:22,729 --> 00:30:24,197
Any luck with Carl Fisher?

00:30:24,264 --> 00:30:25,465
I don't know.

00:30:25,532 --> 00:30:27,367
He wants something from me...

00:30:27,434 --> 00:30:29,736
or he wouldn't still be here.

00:30:57,965 --> 00:31:00,801
♪ ♪

00:31:17,417 --> 00:31:19,419
(machine whirs)

00:31:39,439 --> 00:31:40,440
SANDERS (on phone):
Sanders?

00:31:40,507 --> 00:31:41,875
You can stop gassing up.

00:31:41,942 --> 00:31:43,076
I've got a match.

00:31:43,143 --> 00:31:46,313
AvCon on Buffalo Canyon.
Pump six.

00:31:49,449 --> 00:31:51,385
Where did he board?

00:31:51,451 --> 00:31:52,753
Vegas depot.

00:31:52,819 --> 00:31:54,021
Was he with anyone?

00:31:55,389 --> 00:31:56,890
I'm not gonna
report you.

00:31:56,957 --> 00:31:58,425
You can tell me the truth.

00:31:58,492 --> 00:32:00,394
Children aren't supposed
to travel alone,

00:32:00,460 --> 00:32:02,496
but it was a full bus
when I took off today.

00:32:02,562 --> 00:32:03,797
I couldn't tell you.

00:32:03,864 --> 00:32:05,499
He was definitely
by himself.

00:32:05,565 --> 00:32:07,067
I saw this, I
knew it was him.

00:32:07,134 --> 00:32:08,735
DRIVER:
I radioed my dispatcher.

00:32:08,802 --> 00:32:10,837
She told me to pullover
at the next town,

00:32:10,904 --> 00:32:13,006
make sure he doesn't get off,
and wait for you.

00:32:13,073 --> 00:32:14,508
Thank you for your help.

00:32:14,575 --> 00:32:15,776
Can you tell me

00:32:15,842 --> 00:32:17,411
where he's sitting?
Back row.

00:32:32,926 --> 00:32:34,161
Hey.

00:32:36,263 --> 00:32:38,999
My name's Sofia. Are you Jason?

00:32:41,668 --> 00:32:43,804
There's nothing to be
afraid of, Jason.

00:32:43,870 --> 00:32:46,340
You're not in trouble.
I just want to help you.

00:32:46,406 --> 00:32:49,443
You're on your way
to Texas to see
your dad, right?

00:32:51,745 --> 00:32:53,480
It's just...

00:32:53,547 --> 00:32:54,915
well, went you went missing,

00:32:54,982 --> 00:32:58,151
your dad flew to Las Vegas
to find you.

00:32:58,218 --> 00:33:00,454
He's waiting for you.

00:33:00,520 --> 00:33:02,222
Can I take you to him?

00:33:09,029 --> 00:33:11,331
BROWN:
<i>Is that the tox report</i>
<i>for Lucas Hanson?</i>

00:33:11,398 --> 00:33:13,867
His blood alcohol--
point one six.

00:33:13,934 --> 00:33:16,236
Geez. It's a drunk kid.

00:33:16,303 --> 00:33:18,972
And Sara found a whiskey cap
in Carl Fisher's car.

00:33:19,039 --> 00:33:21,074
Oh, perfect way

00:33:21,141 --> 00:33:23,977
to loosen up a little boy--
give him pizza and whiskey.

00:33:24,044 --> 00:33:25,512
Yeah, well, listen to this.

00:33:25,579 --> 00:33:28,181
According to the report,
Lucas also had 98 micrograms

00:33:28,248 --> 00:33:30,083
per milliliter of salicylates

00:33:30,150 --> 00:33:31,652
in his system.
Well, I guess

00:33:31,718 --> 00:33:33,854
he took the aspirin
after he hit his head.

00:33:33,921 --> 00:33:35,489
Wonder who gave him that.

00:33:35,555 --> 00:33:37,457
Probably the same
responsible adult

00:33:37,524 --> 00:33:39,393
that gave him the whiskey.

00:33:42,462 --> 00:33:46,500
FISHER:
So, you think I got
the boys drunk,

00:33:46,566 --> 00:33:48,068
and then killed them?

00:33:48,135 --> 00:33:50,203
Not exactly.

00:33:50,270 --> 00:33:53,040
We found Jason Crowley.

00:33:53,106 --> 00:33:54,808
Alive.

00:33:54,875 --> 00:33:57,077
On a bus headed
for Houston.

00:33:57,144 --> 00:34:00,080
One of the lucky ones.

00:34:10,724 --> 00:34:13,860
It's okay, Jason.

00:34:13,927 --> 00:34:15,929
Daddy's here, boy.
Daddy's here.

00:34:20,100 --> 00:34:23,437
That bus ticket costs $95
for a child under 12.

00:34:23,503 --> 00:34:26,006
Jason's grandfather
doesn't keep any cash

00:34:26,073 --> 00:34:29,042
in the house, and he doesn't
give him an allowance,

00:34:29,109 --> 00:34:31,612
so where do you think
Jason got the cash?

00:34:31,678 --> 00:34:33,714
Maybe he stole it.

00:34:33,780 --> 00:34:36,049
From whom?
I don't know.

00:34:36,116 --> 00:34:38,285
Why don't you ask him?

00:34:38,352 --> 00:34:40,554
I will.

00:34:43,991 --> 00:34:46,426
Do you get a lot
of migraines, Gil?

00:34:49,062 --> 00:34:52,266
You should ask your doctor for
a prescription of sumatriptan.

00:34:52,332 --> 00:34:54,334
Works for me.

00:34:58,238 --> 00:35:01,074
Captain Brass wants
to put you in a lineup.

00:35:01,141 --> 00:35:03,577
If you'll agree to it,

00:35:03,644 --> 00:35:05,846
then I think
this will all be over with.

00:35:05,913 --> 00:35:08,749
Then let's do it.

00:35:08,815 --> 00:35:10,651
(light switch clacks)

00:35:10,717 --> 00:35:13,320
SOFIA:
Do you recognize
anyone, Jason?

00:35:15,756 --> 00:35:17,524
Which number?

00:35:23,230 --> 00:35:25,165
Number two?

00:35:25,232 --> 00:35:27,267
Yes.

00:35:27,334 --> 00:35:30,170
Was he the man
who kidnapped you and Lucas?

00:35:33,574 --> 00:35:35,976
Jason,

00:35:36,043 --> 00:35:38,612
remember, you can see him,
but he can't see you.

00:35:38,679 --> 00:35:41,448
Did number two
hurt Lucas?

00:35:41,515 --> 00:35:44,785
MAN (distant, distorted):
<i>I'll kill your dad</i>
<i>if you tell...</i>

00:35:44,851 --> 00:35:46,853
No, ma'am.

00:36:00,867 --> 00:36:03,303
The gas DNA panned out.

00:36:03,370 --> 00:36:05,138
It did?

00:36:05,205 --> 00:36:08,175
Yeah. Hodges and I traced
the gas back

00:36:08,242 --> 00:36:10,010
to a service station
near Fisher's house.

00:36:10,077 --> 00:36:11,178
Station had security cameras.

00:36:11,245 --> 00:36:12,512
Got him filling up

00:36:12,579 --> 00:36:15,382
the night of the fire, so I went
through the electronic receipts.

00:36:15,449 --> 00:36:16,717
All of them.

00:36:16,783 --> 00:36:19,219
Carl Fisher purchased
16 gallons.

00:36:19,286 --> 00:36:20,687
And?

00:36:20,754 --> 00:36:22,889
His Mercury Marquis
only holds 14,

00:36:22,956 --> 00:36:24,891
so, where did he put the extra

00:36:24,958 --> 00:36:26,093
two gallons?

00:36:26,159 --> 00:36:28,528
In a plastic gas can?

00:36:28,595 --> 00:36:31,098
All of which he paid for
with his ATM.

00:36:31,164 --> 00:36:32,366
Not the same as cash.

00:36:32,432 --> 00:36:35,402
Thanks, Greg.

00:36:38,639 --> 00:36:42,409
No one has told me
why I'm being detained.

00:36:42,476 --> 00:36:43,810
Arson is a felony.

00:36:43,877 --> 00:36:45,579
You torched your own car.

00:36:45,646 --> 00:36:47,848
We have video
surveillance

00:36:47,915 --> 00:36:51,785
and electronic records
that show you purchasing gas

00:36:51,852 --> 00:36:53,387
and a gas can.

00:36:53,453 --> 00:36:55,489
I was trying
to scam my insurance company.

00:36:55,555 --> 00:36:56,757
I needed the money.

00:36:56,823 --> 00:36:58,158
You were destroying evidence

00:36:58,225 --> 00:37:00,494
of Lucas Hanson
and Jason Crowley in your car.

00:37:02,329 --> 00:37:04,798
And I think
you helped kill Lucas.

00:37:04,865 --> 00:37:06,900
No, I didn't.

00:37:06,967 --> 00:37:10,904
And you're not charging me
for that, so I'm guessing

00:37:10,971 --> 00:37:13,273
Jason didn't pick me
out of the lineup.

00:37:13,340 --> 00:37:15,809
He told us he knew you.

00:37:15,876 --> 00:37:19,479
Kill one, kill both, remember?

00:37:22,015 --> 00:37:24,918
If I <i>had</i> killed Lucas,

00:37:24,985 --> 00:37:27,688
I would have killed Jason.

00:37:29,389 --> 00:37:31,658
(sighs)

00:37:31,725 --> 00:37:34,861
Lucas was looking for a father.

00:37:34,928 --> 00:37:37,631
His real one was an accident
of biology.

00:37:37,698 --> 00:37:39,666
His mother was limited,
always working.

00:37:39,733 --> 00:37:42,970
He was lonely.

00:37:43,036 --> 00:37:44,605
<i>He</i> found <i>me.</i>

00:37:44,671 --> 00:37:48,842
LUCAS:
I see you every day.

00:37:48,909 --> 00:37:52,145
You play a lot, huh?

00:37:52,212 --> 00:37:53,780
Maybe we can play sometime.

00:37:55,682 --> 00:37:57,451
My best friend's
always grounded.

00:37:57,517 --> 00:37:58,518
How about tomorrow?

00:38:02,756 --> 00:38:04,191
Did you know

00:38:04,258 --> 00:38:06,860
that most parents spend less
than 20 minutes a day

00:38:06,927 --> 00:38:08,762
of quality time
with their kids?

00:38:08,829 --> 00:38:10,497
Lucas was starved
for attention.

00:38:10,564 --> 00:38:13,000
All his mother did
was complain about his father

00:38:13,066 --> 00:38:14,968
and how he'd abandoned them.

00:38:15,035 --> 00:38:17,437
Do you know
what that does to a child?

00:38:17,504 --> 00:38:19,206
It doesn't kill them.

00:38:21,909 --> 00:38:23,844
Okay, Carl,

00:38:23,911 --> 00:38:25,612
just tell me what happened.

00:38:25,679 --> 00:38:27,748
(sighs)

00:38:27,814 --> 00:38:29,783
Lucas and Jason had gotten
into it

00:38:29,850 --> 00:38:31,685
with Jason's grandfather.

00:38:31,752 --> 00:38:33,520
He knocked
the boys around.

00:38:33,587 --> 00:38:36,857
They ran to Lucas' house,
but couldn't get in,

00:38:36,924 --> 00:38:38,558
so they came to me.

00:38:38,625 --> 00:38:39,726
(knocking)

00:38:41,428 --> 00:38:44,231
(crickets chirping)

00:38:44,298 --> 00:38:46,733
<i>I explained to them</i>
<i>that hitting wasn't okay.</i>

00:38:46,800 --> 00:38:48,735
I said Jason needed
to call his father

00:38:48,802 --> 00:38:50,470
and tell him what was going on.

00:38:50,537 --> 00:38:52,239
Did you let them
use your phone?

00:38:52,306 --> 00:38:53,640
But they were too upset.

00:38:53,707 --> 00:38:57,144
When the grandfather
pushed Lucas, he hit his head.

00:38:57,210 --> 00:38:59,146
I gave him a couple
of aspirin.

00:38:59,212 --> 00:39:01,081
Well, if he didn't want
to call his mother,

00:39:01,148 --> 00:39:02,249
why didn't you call her?

00:39:02,316 --> 00:39:03,483
I couldn't risk it.

00:39:03,550 --> 00:39:05,085
She might have turned me in.

00:39:05,152 --> 00:39:07,588
So, instead,
you took them for pizza?

00:39:07,654 --> 00:39:10,390
I didn't touch him.

00:39:10,457 --> 00:39:12,392
I didn't want to hurt him.

00:39:12,459 --> 00:39:13,860
You gave him liquor.

00:39:13,927 --> 00:39:16,096
I stopped and bought
some whiskey before we picked up

00:39:16,163 --> 00:39:18,599
the pizza-- I was nervous about
them being in the car with me.

00:39:18,665 --> 00:39:20,233
I didn't want
to go back to prison.

00:39:20,300 --> 00:39:21,768
And you wanted
to get them drunk.

00:39:23,470 --> 00:39:26,907
They... They just wanted
to try it.

00:39:26,974 --> 00:39:28,942
I gave them a taste.

00:39:29,009 --> 00:39:32,079
GRISSOM:
<i>It was more than a taste, Carl.</i>

00:39:32,145 --> 00:39:34,214
<i>Lucas' blood alcohol level</i>
<i>was point one six.</i>

00:39:34,281 --> 00:39:36,750
<i>That's twice the legal limit</i>
<i>for an adult.</i>

00:39:38,318 --> 00:39:40,520
Why didn't you take them home?

00:39:40,587 --> 00:39:42,322
They didn't want to go home.

00:39:42,389 --> 00:39:44,791
They wanted an adventure.

00:39:44,858 --> 00:39:46,093
<i>I promised them a dollar</i>

00:39:46,159 --> 00:39:47,894
<i>for every golf ball</i>
<i>they brought back.</i>

00:39:47,961 --> 00:39:50,564
<i>Lucas wasn't feeling well, so</i>
<i>he stayed in the car with me.</i>

00:39:50,631 --> 00:39:53,233
GRISSOM:
<i>And you knew that Jason</i>
<i>wanted money, so he could go</i>

00:39:53,300 --> 00:39:55,102
<i>to Texas and see his dad,</i>

00:39:55,168 --> 00:39:57,571
so you bribed him in order

00:39:57,638 --> 00:39:58,939
to be alone
with Lucas.

00:39:59,006 --> 00:40:00,374
I didn't molest him.

00:40:00,440 --> 00:40:01,708
Who took his shirt off?

00:40:01,775 --> 00:40:03,744
He was hot.
What were you
gonna do to him

00:40:03,810 --> 00:40:05,045
once his shirt was off?

00:40:05,112 --> 00:40:06,780
It was innocent.

00:40:06,847 --> 00:40:08,415
He wasn't feeling well.

00:40:08,482 --> 00:40:10,417
He laid

00:40:10,484 --> 00:40:12,653
his head in my lap.

00:40:14,655 --> 00:40:17,457
I touched his hair.

00:40:17,524 --> 00:40:20,360
I didn't want to...

00:40:22,362 --> 00:40:25,832
I loved him.

00:40:25,899 --> 00:40:27,834
I loved Lucas,
and he loved me.

00:40:27,901 --> 00:40:29,770
Is that what you think?

00:40:29,836 --> 00:40:33,173
Then why didn't
you help him?

00:40:33,240 --> 00:40:35,142
He told you he hit his head.

00:40:35,208 --> 00:40:37,344
He was in pain.

00:40:37,411 --> 00:40:38,879
He had a concussion, Carl.

00:40:38,946 --> 00:40:40,414
You must have
known that.

00:40:40,480 --> 00:40:42,516
I'm sure he was dizzy,
probably had no appetite.

00:40:42,583 --> 00:40:44,184
Maybe he was even
slurring his words,

00:40:44,251 --> 00:40:46,086
but you didn't
care about that,

00:40:46,153 --> 00:40:49,256
because you wanted
what you wanted.

00:40:49,323 --> 00:40:51,458
(panting)

00:40:51,525 --> 00:40:53,961
Lucas?!

00:40:54,027 --> 00:40:56,296
GRISSOM:
<i>His brain was bleeding.</i>

00:40:56,363 --> 00:40:58,198
Now, most kids won't die
from that,

00:40:58,265 --> 00:40:59,933
because someone
who really loves them

00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:01,301
takes them to the hospital,

00:41:01,368 --> 00:41:04,371
but instead, you gave him
alcohol and aspirin,

00:41:04,438 --> 00:41:06,640
a lethal combination
for his head injury.

00:41:06,707 --> 00:41:09,977
It prevented his
blood from clotting.

00:41:10,043 --> 00:41:13,614
You killed him, Carl.

00:41:13,680 --> 00:41:19,219
<i>And you would have killed</i>
<i>Jason, too,</i>

00:41:19,286 --> 00:41:23,724
<i>except he ran away from you</i>
<i>and crawled into a drain pipe.</i>

00:41:29,796 --> 00:41:31,298
Hey.

00:41:31,365 --> 00:41:32,666
(panting)

00:41:32,733 --> 00:41:34,868
Hey, what are you
doing in there?

00:41:34,935 --> 00:41:36,203
You're not listening to me.

00:41:36,270 --> 00:41:38,505
I didn't want to hurt anyone.

00:41:38,572 --> 00:41:41,541
I need you to believe me.

00:41:41,608 --> 00:41:43,543
I don't.

00:41:43,610 --> 00:41:45,312
You had choices.

00:41:45,379 --> 00:41:47,981
You made the wrong ones.

00:41:48,048 --> 00:41:51,752
And now this little boy is gone.

00:41:58,392 --> 00:42:00,327
BRASS:
<i>So I talked Voris</i>

00:42:00,394 --> 00:42:01,728
into violating parole,

00:42:01,795 --> 00:42:03,730
and we're adding the charges
of negligent homicide.

00:42:03,797 --> 00:42:05,699
You're not gonna see
Carl for a long time.

00:42:05,766 --> 00:42:09,002
Also, we, uh...
we've arrested

00:42:09,069 --> 00:42:11,505
the grandpa, Terrance
Crowley, for child abuse.

00:42:11,572 --> 00:42:13,840
Everybody wins.

00:42:13,907 --> 00:42:15,876
Except Lucas.

00:42:15,943 --> 00:42:18,445
You're gonna fry.

00:42:18,512 --> 00:42:20,013
You drove him
right to it...!

00:42:20,080 --> 00:42:21,014
You did this!

00:42:21,081 --> 00:42:23,050
You did this!
I'll kill you!

00:42:25,419 --> 00:42:27,821
MARGARET FINN:
Where is Carl Fisher?

00:42:27,888 --> 00:42:29,790
You can't take
him to County...

00:42:29,856 --> 00:42:31,959
Mr. Crowley's
civil rights were violated.

00:42:32,025 --> 00:42:33,760
This department
is racist.

00:42:33,827 --> 00:42:35,395
FINN:
Excuse me! I
was here first.

00:42:35,462 --> 00:42:36,797
My client has been
detained illegally.

00:42:36,863 --> 00:42:39,099
LEWIS:
You cannot
charge Mister...

00:42:52,713 --> 00:42:54,915
(faint, indistinct voices
and laughter in the distance)

00:43:09,796 --> 00:43:11,932
(sighs)

